The paper presents a computationally efficient algorithm for Nonnegative Coupled Matrix Tensor Factorization (N-CMTF), which is a popular technique in machine learning and data analysis. The paper discusses the theoretical and empirical analyses of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it is more accurate and computationally efficient than existing algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
